  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This page is to describe the relationship between ECU Mode Manager and SUM_SUSD"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "SUSD role in Shutdown sequence"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/1.0%20VCU%20Plus%20-%20SUSD%20with%20EcuModeManager/image-2024-8-12_11-26-12.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/1.0 VCU Plus - SUSD with EcuModeManager/image-2024-8-12_11-26-12.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "During the Init sequence, there is no relationship between SUSD and EcuModeManger."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "EcuModeManager along with EcuM and BswM, will propagate to SOC_RUN after Powering up all the necessary peripherals as shown in below State machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "But for the Shutdown sequence, It is always initiated by SUM_SUSD."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The Application State Manager function of SUM_SUSD is responsible to implement this decision. SUM_SUSD makes this decision based on receiving notifications from project specific SW-C via the <SUM/SWC>_SUSD_ShutdownPermission interface. Once SUM_SUSD determines that a shutdown of the ECU is required, it issues the corresponding mode request to BswM"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Configuration of Shutdown Permission"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We need to configure the Shutdown permission ports in ASM, which can hold the SUM state moving to SLEEP when there is no Wakeup sources"
    },
    {
